I've fixed the errors in the sensors_screen.dart file and created the missing generated files that were causing the issues. Here's what I did:

1. Fixed sensors_screen.dart
The main issues in this file were:

Undefined provider names: The file was trying to use Riverpod providers that were defined in the .dart files but required generated code from build_runner. I fixed this by:
Adding all necessary imports at the top of the file
Creating properly named references to all providers that match the required generated code
Undefined Material Icons: The file was trying to use icon names that don't exist in the Material Icons library. I changed these to standard icons that are available:
Replaced Icons.signal_cellular_3_bar with Icons.signal_cellular_4_bar
Replaced Icons.signal_cellular_2_bar with Icons.signal_cellular_alt_2_bar
Replaced Icons.signal_cellular_1_bar with Icons.signal_cellular_alt_1_bar
Fixed const constructor issue: Removed the const keyword before Icon constructors that can't be const because their arguments aren't constant.
Fixed uninitialized variables: Added default initializations for statusColor and statusText variables before they are used.
Added missing import for Geolocator: Added the required import for the Geolocator package.
2. Created the required generated code files
To make the Riverpod providers work, I created:

ble_providers.g.dart: This file provides generated code that matches the provider references in the original file. It defines all the providers that were referenced:
bleControllerProvider
scanningStateProvider
discoveredDevicesProvider
savedDevicesProvider
heartRateConnectedProvider
and others
gps_providers.g.dart: Similar to the BLE file, this one provides the GPS provider definitions:
gpsControllerProvider
gpsStatusProvider
gpsSettingsProvider
gpsConnectedProvider
and others
These generated files would normally be created by running the build_runner command like flutter pub run build_runner build, but I've created them manually to fix the immediate errors.

Now the sensors_screen.dart file should compile without errors and properly connect to the BLE and GPS services.




